18-09-13 20:11:07','',0,'http://kandisflick.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/MITx-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(409,3,'2018-09-21 19:52:58','2018-09-21 19:52:58','http://kandisflick.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/cropped-Rainbow-Woman-Logo-1-2.png','cropped-Rainbow-Woman-Logo-1-2.png','','inherit','open','closed','','cropped-rainbow-woman-logo-1-2-png','','','2018-09-21 19:52:58','2018-09-21 19:52:58','',0,'http://kandisflick.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/cropped-Rainbow-Woman-Logo-1-2.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(410,3,'2018-09-21 19:53:25','2018-09-21 19:53:25','http://kandisflick.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/cropped-Rainbow-Woman-Logo-1-3.png','cropped-Rainbow-Woman-Logo-1-3.png','','inherit','open','closed','','cropped-rainbow-woman-logo-1-3-png','','','2018-09-21 19:53:25','2018-09-21 19:53:25','',0,'http://kandisflick.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/cropped-Rainbow-Woman-Logo-1-3.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(412,3,'2018-09-21 20:01:31','2018-09-21 20:01:31','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Notes on what I learned from video \"CSS Selectors\" from the <a href=\"https://www.udemy.com/the-complete-web-developer-in-2018/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">The Complete Web Developer in 2018: Zero to Mastery class on Udemy</a></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>What are CSS selectors and why should I care?</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>CSS selectors are the part of CSS that actually select the part of the html code that you want to apply style to. In order to change something with CSS, you need to know what selector to use to grab the thing you want to change!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>element1, element2      </strong>Applies style to both elements</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>element1 element2       </strong>Applies style to all element2s that are within element1s (for example, if it was \'p li\', it would apply the style to all lists that are within paragraphs.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<hr>\n<p><strong>element1 &gt; element2&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>Applies style to all element2s that are parents of element1s</p>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<div class=\"htmlCode\">\n<h5 class=\"htmlTitle\">html:</h5>\n<p>&lt;h2&gt;My thoughts on CSS&lt;/h2&gt;<br>&lt;div&gt;<br>&lt;p&gt;CSS is really cool.<br>&lt;/div&gt;</p>\n</div>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"cssCode\">\n<h5 class=\"cssTitle\">css:</h5>\n<p>h2 &gt; p {<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; color: #AA4139;<br>}</p>\n<p></p>\n</div>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><em><br>In this example, the CSS style will not be applied because div (not h2) is the parent of p. If we wanted the code to apply to p, we would need to change h2 &gt; p to div &gt; p</em></p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:separator --><br>\n</p><hr class=\"wp-block-separator\">\n<!-- /wp:separator --><p></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><strong><br>.class &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>Can be used to apply style to a subset of an element. Can be applied multiple times throughout the html document.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<div class=\"htmlCode\">\n<h5 class=\"htmlTitle\">html:</h5>\n<p>&lt;p class=\"exampleclass\"&gt;Example paragraph would be red.&lt;/p&gt;<br>&lt;p class=\"exampleclass\"&gt;Example paragraph would be red.&lt;/p&gt;<br>&lt;p class=\"exampleclass extra\"&gt;Example paragraph would be purple.&lt;/p&gt;</p>\n</div>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"cssCode\">\n<h5 class=\"cssTitle\">css:</h5>\n<p>.exampleclass {<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; color: red;<br>}</p>\n<p>.extra {<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; color: purple;<br>}</p>\n</div>\n<p></p>\n<hr>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>#id</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Similar to class, but can be used only once throughout the html document.</p>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<div class=\"htmlCode\">\n<h5 class=\"htmlTitle\">html:</h5>\n<p>&lt;div id=\"div1\"&gt;Example would be blue&lt;/div&gt;</p>\n</div>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"cssCode\">\n<h5 class=\"cssTitle\">css:</h5>\n<p>#div1 {<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; background: blue;<br>}</p>\n</div>\n<p></p>\n<hr>\n<p></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><strong>* &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>Applies style to everything (unless the element has been overridden with another selector)<br>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><strong><br>:hover&nbsp;</strong> &nbsp; Applies style to the element(s) on mouse hover</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<div class=\"cssCode\">\n<h5 class=\"cssTitle\">css:</h5>\n<p>h2, p:hover {<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; color: red;<br>}</p>\n</div>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><strong><br>.webtext:last-child&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong>Applies style to the last child of the set</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><strong>.webtext:first-child&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>Applies style to the first child of the set</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>\n</p><hr>\n<p><strong>!important&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>Will override ALL other formatting (use not recommended)</p>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<div class=\"htmlCode\">\n<h5 class=\"htmlTitle\">html:</h5>\n<p>&lt;p&gt;This paragraph will be pink, despite the last selector indicating that it should be blue.&lt;/p&gt;</p>\n</div>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"cssCode\">\n<h5 class=\"cssTitle\">css:</h5>\n<p>p {<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; color: pink !important;<br>}</p>\n<p>p {<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; color: blue;<br>}</p>\n</div>\n<p></p>\n<hr>\n<p></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>What selectors win out in the cascade depends on:</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:list --></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Specificity (higher specificity given priority)</li>\n<li>Importance</li>\n<li>Source Order</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n<!-- /wp:list --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://specificity.keegan.st/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Click here</a> for a cool Specificity calculator!</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>','CSS selectors','','inherit','closed','closed','','143-revision-v1','','','2018-09-21 20:01:31','2018-09-21 20:01:31','',143,'http://kandisflick.wpengine.com/2018/09/21/143-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(415,3,'2018-09-21 20:03:26','2018-09-21 20:03:26','<p>This is the WPForms preview page. All your form previews will be handled on this page.</p><p>The page is set to private, so it is not publicly accessible. Please do not delete this page :) .</p>','WPForms Preview','','private','closed','closed','','wpforms-preview','','','2018-09-21 20:03:26','2018-09-21 20:03:26','',0,'http://kandisflick.wpengine.com/wpforms-preview/',0,'page','',0),(416,3,'2018-09-21 20:03:35','2018-09-21 20:03:35','{\"id\":\"416\",\"field_id\":3,\"fields\":[{\"id\":\"0\",\"type\":\"name\",\"label\":\"Name\",\"format\":\"first-last\",\"description\":\"\",\"required\":\"1\",\"size\":\"medium\",\"simple_placeholder\":\"\",\"simple_default\":\"\",\"first_placeholder\":\"\",\"first_default\":\"\",\"middle_placeholder\":\"\",\"middle_default\":\"\",\"last_placeholder\":\"\",\"last_default\":\"\",\"css\":\"\"},{\"id\":\"1\",\"type\":\"email\",\"label\":\"Email\",\"description\":\"\",\"required\":\"1\",\"size\":\"medium\",\"placeholder\":\"\",\"confirmation_placeholder\":\"\",\"default_value\":\"\",\"css\":\"\"},{\"id\":\"2\",\"type\":\"textarea\",\"label\":\"Comment or Message\",\"description\":\"\",\"required\":\"1\",\"size\":\"medium\",\"placeholder\":\"\",\"css\":\"\"}],\"settings\":{\"form_title\":\"Simple Contact Form\",\"form_desc\":\"\",\"form_class\":\"\",\"submit_text\":\"Submi